y metadata file; maybe allPublicMethods should include Object methods? For the interface, does getMethods return public methods, including those inherited from Object? I should clarify that interfaces do not typically include Object methods. Additionally, it seems allPublicMethods on an interface returns just the interface methods. I'll need to check further into the proxy invocation and its requirements.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Identifying issues with methods**\\n\\nI'm considering a potential issue with the methodsMissing on getInterface(Object, Class) regarding NativeObjects from previous evals. What exactly does jsToJava convert NativeObject to? It might just return the NativeObject, which seems fine. If getInterface(Class) ends up returning null for empty class methods, methodsMissing could still lead to a generated proxy. That said, if getMethods returns empty, the tests seem to pass, which is curious. I'll need to assess if the proxy metadata adheres to the old schema under \\\"reflection.\\\"\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking for AGENTS issues**\\n\\nI think I need to check for any AGENTS that have no tests. However, I'm considering if I should mention that they haven't been run yet. Before I finalize everything, it might be helpful to inspect the git diff for any changes. I want to ensure that all necessary tests are accounted for and that nothing is overlooked, especially since it's crucial to have everything running smoothly before proceeding. I’ll make a note to review this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_xq0qlbRcTvp7lp7qiFK3WgOW|fc_00bab92d9bbdf8290169f7ef76f81881a19c2be49c2a6ece21", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/java/net_sourceforge_htmlunit/htmlunit_core_js/RhinoScriptEngineTest.java tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json", "tim